Home    /    People    /    Faculty    /    Supratik Mukhopadhyay 






Supratik Mukhopadhyay
Associate Professor



363 Hatcher Hall



Louisiana State University
Baton Rouge, LA 70803




Phone: 225 578 1496

supratik@csc.lsu.edu

Educational Background
Ph.D. in Computer Science, Max-Plank Institute for Computer Science and University of Saarland, Germany, 2001M.S. in Computer Science, Indian Statistical Institute, Calcutta, 1996
 
Teaching Responsibilities
CSC 3380: Object Oriented DesignCSC 4330: Software System DevelopmentCSC 7150: Program Analysis & Model Checking
 
Selected Publications
Ravindran Kaliappa, Ali Sabbir, Subhajit Sidhanta, and Supratik Mukhopadhyay. Managing Shared Contexts in Distributed Multi-player Game Systems, To appear in Proceedings of IEEE COMSNETS, 2014
M. Peralta and Supratik Mukhopadhyay. Code-Change Impact Analysis Using Counterfactuals, Accepted for publication at the International Journal on Software Engineering and Knowledge Engineering, 2013
Hong Yi Chen, Supratik Mukhopadhyay, and Shaked Flur, Termination Proofs for Linear Simple Loops, Accepted to the Journal Software Tools for Technology Transfer (Springer Verlag), 2013
Chris Alvin, Sumit Gulwani, Rupak Majumdar, and Supratik Mukhopadhyay,  Synthesis of Geometry Proof Problems, In Proceedings of AAAI, 2014 
Hongyi Chen, Supratik Mukhopadhyay, and Zheng Lu, Control Flow Renement and Symbolic Computation of Average Case Bound, In Proceedings of ATVA 2013, Lecture Notes In Computer Science (LNCS), Springer Verlag, 2013
 
